rComments:
WARNING to political science students. 

This is not a political science professor, I took his 4th year seminar course on Canadian politics and it was solely about gender and race studies.

Orsini's extensive knowledge in the politics of health is really impressive. However, I found that he had difficulty conveying the material and getting his point across in lectures. He's really nice, funny and even brought us food on multiple occasions! Come to class and do the readings.

Fyi: 1) the course I took was part of the MA/PhD in fem and gender studies 2) this course was a seminar 3) the subject was Critical Dis/ability Studies At first I found that this prof was hard to size up. It turns out that unlike what other comments said, he's not a jerk at all. Makes you work (too hard?) for your grade but the class was great.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: good guy, not very organized but that being said i would have him again no problem.

This teacher was able to make a dry subject quite enjoyable and he's definitely much better than the two other politics profs that I've had. He's always happy to help you out if you don't understand something but you do have to work hard for your mark.

At first I thought he just had a dry sarcastic sense of humour but I later found out that he just has a terrible attitude. AVOID AT ALL COSTS. Marking is EXTREMELY inconsistent and arbitrary and to top it off, he can't seem to get his thoughts out in his lectures - It's like pulling teeth waiting for him to form a sentence. AVOID AT ALL COSTS.

I read that prof. Orsini relied to much on powerpoints!? there was no pouwerpoints whatsoever in our class, the course pack was humongous, and the marking very harsh. too bad, because he's a really nice guy. my paper was defenitly worth more than 66% it was better than that ted marmor article which had absolutely no facts in it...

The courses relied heavily on overloaded Powerpoint slides, but these were availible online prior to the course. The professor's sense of humour made a very dry subject (Even for someone majoring in Politics) interesting. He was very approachable and understanding of difficulties students may have had.
quite hard class. the prof asked for quite much, a lot of works considering it was a second year course. but he was helpful and willing to help.

This is supposed to be political science not journalism. Furthermore, he is overly preoccupied with the jargon and pointless details of health politics and policy in order to earn his right as an objective and scientific political thinker. His contribution to the field of study - hardly noticed up to now, at the end of the day - trivial.

I was unsure what this class would be like...but I ended up really enjoying this class. At first the assignments and HUGE course packs are a bit intimidating but I only read about 10 of the reading, but attended every class and still got a good mark. I would recommend this prof!

I disagree with all of these comments. He's not terrible, nor is he a godsend. He's a reasonable prof who understands POL 2101 is full of idiots. He is very clear with both material and expectations, which is great. Sometimes the class moves very slowly, but such is life. I would recommend because he is always willing to help students in every way.
Worst professor I've ever had in 4 years at U of O. Avoid at all costs.
Needs a new personality.  Has the immediate ability to be a big jerk!  His disposition when it comes to things are very negative and really has a bad attitude
awesome prof!!! doesn't take himself too seriously! adds humour to a dry subject!! it's a privilege to take his course!
I think Professor Orsini is an excellent professor - no matter what the other students might say!  He is very helpful, smart, and also very funny.  I am very happy to have him as my professor.
It isn't hard to have a grasp on Canadian Politics. Is too critical toward the Canadian System, never has anything nice to say about our country. There is nothing worse than ex-journalists
GUys is geat, reminds of the critic, more in touch wiht Canadian Politics than most people, easliy the most appraochable teachers in the department. Toush/Fair A++

Oh come on! It's refreshing to have a prof who not only has complete command of his field, but has a good sense of humor and isn't afraid to speak his mind. Totally approachable and a tough but fair marker, Orsini is one of the best in the department.

Probably the worst prof ever to have walked on this planet. If you take university education Seriously, avoir Orsini at all cost!! I feel like I'm being taught by a 16 year old. I mean, he giggles everytime he says the word "member". Come on!
Funny guy...   He seems to be pretty hip with what's going on in the world of reality TV.  Only prof i've ever heard make a comment about this website in his lectures!  (oh yeah he's ... hot!)
Nothing sadder than a prof. who rates himself on this website. Just look at the other comments!
Gotta love the dry humour and cynicism; power points are a definite plus; and he is super hot!
-makes very very very boring material interesting- good sense of homour
He is sooooooooo hot!! Only complaint is office hours - the lineup of hotties to see him is often hours long! Other than that, what can I say? He's hot - take his class!
I love his sense of humour! it's makes it worthwhile to get up in the morning for an 8:30.  That and the fear of the pop quiz...
excellent overall, but makes you work hard for marks. Really helps to prepare you for midterms/finals!
there ya go!
tough marker, good lecturer

Orsini knows his stuff very well. His lectures tend to rely too much on power point, though they're still interesting. Highly recommended - can't wait to take his health policy course, whenever it's approved by the department.
